Presiding officers of parliament, Thandi Modise and Amos Masondo will appear at the Zondo Commission today as parliamentary oversight evidence continues being heard. Editor's note: This Livestream has ended. You may watch the recording above. Courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - The state capture inquiry continues on Monday, despite the burglary at its head offices at the weekend. The Zondo Commission will hear testimony from the Speaker of the National Assembly, Thandi Modise, and the National Council of Provinces' Amos Masondo. READ: State Capture Burglary : 'We are not intimidated' - Mosala The commission is questioning the motive for the break-in at its offices in Parktown, Johannesburg. It's still trying to ascertain if anything other than a computer and monitor was stolen.